Validations.
   - AngularJS By Default Supports the Form Validations.
   - when ever error raised in form, automatically corresponding error will store in "$error" object by framework.


Text Validation.

<form name="myForm">

    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>

    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Minimum 3 characters are required****</h5>
    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">***Maximum 6 characters are Allowed****</h5>
    <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank****</h5>
</form>


Validations by using mgMessages Module
-

    - ngMessages is the Predefined Module used to handle the Validations.

    - ngMessages Module eliminates the Duplicate Code.


Step 1.
    Add the ngMessages Dependency.

Example_2.html
-

<html ng-app="app">

    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.6.0/angular.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/angular-messages/1.6.4/angular-messages.min.js"><script>
    <script>
        var app = angular.module("app",["ngMessages"]);
    </script>
</html>



Step 2.
    Create the Validation messages with the help of "ng-message" directive.

messages.html
-
<div ng-message="required">****Can't Left Blank****</div>
<div ng-message="minlength">****Minimum 3 Characters are required****</div>
<div ng-message="maxlength">****Maximum 6 Chacters are Allowed****</div>
<div ng-message="email">****Please enter the valid email****</div>
<div ng-message="pattern">****Please enter the valid phone number****</div>


Step 3.

    Import the Validations File(messages.html).


Example_2.html
-

<form name="myForm">

    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>

    <div ng-messages="myForm.uname.$error">
        <div ng-messages-include="messages.html"></div>
    </div>
</form>







